<div class="library-tome-centered">
Eleven Labs is an incredible tool for content creators, offering features like voice cloning that allow me to capture my voice in all my blog posts. This capability lets me convert my writings into audio and then into videos, making it incredibly easy to produce content. However, the platform's limitations pose significant challenges.<div><br></div><div>Currently, the 4-minute daily limit on usage impacts my workflow and creativity. I can't write as much as I want and convert it to video without hitting the cap quickly. This constraint forces me to limit my output, which stifles my ability to create freely. Despite paying for the creator plan, which costs $22 USD per month, I find the allocated compute time insufficient.</div><div><br></div><div>A typical day using Eleven Labs involves making a single love letter to Ivory, which consumes most of my daily limit. While this is valuable, it feels limiting since I could easily record such a short piece with my own voice. I aspire to create longer posts and convert those into audio, but the current pricing and usage restrictions make this difficult.</div><div><br></div><div>If I had unlimited access to Eleven Labs, I would turn almost all my writings into videos. My videos would become mirrors of my writings, delving deeper into topics and allowing me to explore them further on camera. This seamless integration would significantly enhance my content creation process.</div><div><br></div><div>I haven't found any alternatives that match Eleven Labs' quality. I don't want to sacrifice quality for a cheaper option. The technology they provide is unmatched, and I appreciate their work. However, the compute cost needs to be more affordable for creators. Until compute becomes cheaper and allows for more generous usage limits, this problem will persist.</div><div><br></div><div>In conclusion, while Eleven Labs offers fantastic tools for content creators, the current limitations hinder the creative process. A more generous compute allocation at the current price point would make a significant difference, allowing creators like me to produce more and better content without worrying about hitting limits.</div><div><br></div><div>Visit [wendellsdiary.com](https://wendellsdiary.com) for more content and to follow my journey.</div>
</div>
